els-Spider-Man-2-Cind-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Marvels-Spider-Man-2-Cind-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Marvels-Spider-Man-2-Cind-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Marvels-Spider-Man-2-Cind-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/marvels-spider-man"><em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man</em></a> voice actor Yuri Lowenthal has confirmed a third game in the hit series is in the works, and will still feature a lot of Peter Parker.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE:</strong> <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/game-reviews/marvels-spider-man-2-review-3513197">&#39;Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2&#39; review: a new standard for superhero games</a></li></ul><p> <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man</em> was released in 2018 before <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/marvels-spider-man-2">a sequel</a> followed in 2023 that ended with Peter Parker handing the mantle of Spider-Man to Miles Morales. A third entry in the series has yet to be confirmed by developers Insomniac but narrative director Ben Arfmann has spoken about the possibility of a <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/marvels-spider-man-2-didnt-use-90-per-cent-of-recorded-venom-dialogue-3549570">Venom spin-off</a> while senior creative director Bryan Intihar said a third game would be “pretty epic”.</p><p> Now Peter Parker&#39;s voice actor Yuri Lowenthal has seemingly confirmed the third <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man</em> game is currently being developed. Speaking to <a href="https://thedirect.com/article/spider-man-3-ps5-game-story-exclusive" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Direct</a> , he said: “There are very few things that I can say about this game, but you have somehow landed on the one thing that I can answer, and that&#39;s that, yes, Peter is not gone. He will be a part of the next game and he won&#39;t be relegated to the couch, I promise.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2 - Story Trailer | PS5游戏" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/bgqGdIoa52s?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Earlier this year, a job listing at Insomniac Games suggested <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 3</em> had started pre-production but the studio is currently focusing most of its efforts on the upcoming <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/marvels-wolverine"><em>Marvel&#39;s Wolverine</em></a> , which is rumoured to be released next year.</p><p> Speaking about Miles Morales becoming the main Spider-Man at the end of the second game, writer Brittney Morris said (via <em><a href="https://gizmodo.com/spider-man-2-ps5-spoilers-interview-venom-miles-cindy-1850955935" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gizmodo</a></em> ): “It always felt very natural, and I think we all collectively thought it would happen.对我来说，它显示了迈尔斯的大量进化。在游戏开始时，我们看到他努力弄清楚他想对自己的生活做什么。 By the end, we had Miles carrying the burden of saving the city, and also carrying Pete when Pete wasn&#39;t strong enough to carry himself at various points.</p><p> “That&#39;s what&#39;s been so cool about writing a story about two Spider-Men: they&#39;re both strong, and one of them can be strong when the other is not. By the end, Miles is more confident and he&#39;s like, &#39;Yeah, I got this. How much worse can things get after what we just went through?&#39;”</p><p> In other news, Tony Hawk has <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/tony-hawk-responds-to-rumours-of-a-new-pro-skater-game-3840736">responded to the many rumours</a> that a new <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/tony-hawks-pro-skater">Pro Skater</a></em> game is set to be unveiled in the coming weeks.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/marvel