horizon-knocked-loose-3839045">Speaking to <em>NME</em> recently</a> , A Day To Remember&#39;s Jeremy McKinnon told us how he was excited to play in his home state of Florida. “It definitely makes it easy OK guys, I&#39;ve got to drop my kid off this morning, but I&#39;ll be over there around seven o&#39;clock. I&#39;m kidding, I don&#39;t know what slot they&#39;re going to have us,” he said.</p><p> “For them to be in Florida, it just makes sense,” he continued. “有趣的故事，实际上，一旦他们最初宣布，我们就不在佛罗里达州。 All of a sudden, people were like &#39;Oh my God, A Day To Remember are playing Florida!&#39; We were like &#39;Uh oh, some people are gonna be mad…&#39; but then they came back to us and said, &#39;Why don&#39;t you play Florida?&#39; Sounds like a good idea.”</p><p> The Warped Tour has been going since 1995, and became known as the Vans Warped Tour a year later for sponsorship reasons. It <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/warped-tour-end-2018-obituary-2364152">made its final tour across the US in 2018</a> , before a toned-down festival the following year to celebrate its 25th anniversary.</p><p> Founder Kevin Lyman announced last autumn that the punk, pop-punk, emo and alternative rock event would be returning for 2025. He told <a href="https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/vans-warped-tour-2025-kevin-lyman-1235131851/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Rolling Stone</em></a> at the time: “People start remembering once something&#39;s gone that it was important, it was fun – and I&#39;m hoping to recapture a lot of that again.”</p><p> Lyman also said that, while his “body won&#39;t take riding around on a tour bus” to the number of cities the tour would visit in its heyday, he&#39;d be open to adding more dates in future years if 2025 turned out to成功。</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/a-day-to-remember-silverstein-motion-city-soundtrack-lead-new-names-added-to-returning-vans-warped-tour-2025-3840782">A Day To Remember, Silverstein, Motion City Soundtrack lead new names added to returning Vans Warped Tour 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
